# TypeScript Interface-First Rules

- Use `interface` for component props and for function or hook argument objects.
- Define these interfaces in the same file as the component/hook/function by default.
- Extract interfaces to shared files only when reused by multiple modules.
- Use `type` only when interface capabilities are insufficient (e.g. unions, mapped types, advanced composition).

## Example
- Prefer `interface UserCardProps { ... }` over `type UserCardProps = { ... }` for component props.
